    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "The `pendingBlocks` structure is like:\r\n```\r\npending/fetching block n => downloaded/processing block n + 1 => downloaded block n + 2 => ...\r\n```\r\n\r\nCurrently, the 1st block is expected to be ~~a pending~~ an unknown block, then we download block from there, process the downloaded block then the whole chain segment. Since there are too many `pendingBlocks`, `pruneSetToMax` gets called and prune the 1st ~~pending~~ unknown block then UnknownBlockSync is stuck\r\n\r\nThis shows block cache size is always 100, which means it pruned some first blocks and all blocks are downloaded blocks only\r\n\r\n<img width=\"1306\" alt=\"Screenshot 2023-06-16 at 10 41 36\" src=\"https://github.com/ChainSafe/lodestar/assets/10568965/e100b409-aa71-42ae-aefe-a7cf2802ab73\">\r\n\r\nWe should handle this case when there are downloaded blocks only",
